[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering a potential issue with multi-header values from HttpURLConnection, where values like "one, two" may combine into a single string. This could lead to problems when asserting, as it might fail if the list only has "one, two." I need to look into how HttpURLConnection handles repeated headers and whether it often combines them. I think it would be better to assert that the joined string contains both values instead of using `assertThat(included.header("X-Multi")).contains("one", "two");`.
